fields.physical_description:
1.  envelope, white paper
2.  game card, 2 pages of printed cream card with light green surround.   Page one has 63 square slots for the pips plus 13 slots for spares.  The squares are cream edged in black with one green tinted square in the centre which is the Starting Point of the game.  Page two holds the pips, set of spades, hearts, diamonds and clubs.  Written down the middle are the scoring instructions.  On the back of the Ourgo game card is the object of the game.
3-15.  green pips, SPADES, numbered from 1 to 10, jack, queen, king
16-28. pink pips, HEARTS,  numbered 1 to 10, jack, queen, king
29-41. yellow pips, DIAMONDS, numbered 1 to 10, jack, queen, king
42-54. light blue pips, CLUBS, numbered 1 to 10, jack, queen, king
*55-67. spare pips to be used as replacements should any be lost
55-57. blank yellow Diamond pips
58-60. blank green Spade pips
61-64. blank light blue Club pips
65.  light blue Club pip numbered 8
66,67. blank pink Hearts pips
fields.title: ourgo pocket poker game
fields.marks:
OURGO "The New Game Based on the Age-Old Game of Poker Patience

B. Foskett, written on front of game card
fields.history_note:
References: The object of the game is to get the maximum score possible by placing 25 pips in five rows of five each.  

The game belonged to the donor's grandfather.

Made by: Robinson & Sons, Ltd., Chesterfield, England
